day 365 of 365, thank you God 🫶🏽 #2022
—
this past year has been a year of firsts that are definitely preparing me for this next chapter of life. i traveled across the globe a few times doing what i love, started therapy, worked with some of the most amazing clients, had covid TWICE 😭, partnered with some of my fav brands, got heavily into my creative bag, started some new business relationships, went through a dark summer, had some majorrrrrr career firsts, but most importantly i started to bet more on ME & trust God alottttttt more.

three key lessons i’ve learned this year are: you’ve gotta trust yourself a lottttttt more than you give yourself credit for, stopppp operating in fear and understand that setting boundaries are OK!

we’ve only got one life, so cheers to an abundant 2023 🥂

man, the amount of love from everybody over the wknd around a bob, a freaking bobbbbbbb was insane lol. i must say, the hands get to WORK, even though i almost cut a finger off cause i was so damn nervous 😬 

thank you miss kelly for giving me the opportunity to create with you and always pouring so much love+positivity into me, seriously. thank y’all for the love on how clean, symmetrical & precise this goddam bob was cause lord knows i kept saying in my head “this shit BETTER turn out perfect or my ass is grass!”

butttt, here’s the breakdown:
-start with freshly clean hair (mainly for movement)
-blowout+press out your hair (i used a @dysonhair dryer & @eapheat flat iron)
-cut for your LIFE (no product just yet)
-once the cut is done, spray some @ogx_beauty multi-benefit hairspray in the palms of your hands and press that into the top of the head to tame fly aways. (i do this to avoid too much product)
-do the same above with a little oil
-spray some sheen a few inches away from the hair & there you have it ☺️

ps. i’m one of god’s fav, so there’s no stopping me 😌💅🏽
#kellyrowland #kahhspence #rocnationbrunch #hairinspo

THEE Sheryl Lee Ralph 🥂🖤
truthfully, i think my mother, grandmother & whole damn family/tribe would be proud to know i’ve had the pleasure of working with ms. @thesherylleeralph. yes, hair by yours truly for this queen 💁🏽‍♂️

one random day in january, i hit my boy @walkgoodetienne & let him know i’d love to work with his mother because she was on my “dream client list.” waited a couple weeks, but didn’t hear anything & decided to leave it alone; i kept reminding myself “if it’s meant to be, it’ll be!” mayb a few days later, her daughter & stylist @ivycoco23 followed me back and i pitched myself again..then boom, here we are. 

lately i’ve been in this space of practicing patience, gratitude & stillness. the year ‘23 didn’t start exactly how i had planned it, but it’s because god knew there was a different path for me to take on my journey. i’m just so grateful for every blessing & opportunity he brings my way because i’m nothing without him frfr. my time is here, my time is now & i ain’t ever ever ever letting up!

ps. anybody that knows me KNOWS when i first start working with a client i get sooooo nervous & boy was i sweating lol. how do y’all think i did for my first time? 👀

While social media is a place to express yourself authentically with your community, it is also a place to create a relationship with brands. 

@kahhspence navigates this well and share how he does it on @ittakesavillagepod : Episode 17: Success is Where Opportunity and Intention Meet ft. Kahh Spence

 @kahhspence is a hair stylist, with a client list including incredible humans Jhene Aiko , Kelly Rowland, Ella Mai and Kehlani. His work is beautiful and inspiring but his personality is what drew me in. 
 
In this episode we discuss:

*how to balance being both influential and a hair artist. 
*collaborating with friends 
*how to show up for a client that becomes a friend
*how to pitch yourself to brands 
*being a creative director for your personal brand
*how to invest in yourself 
*building a personal brand 
*how to work with any company. 

Click the link in my bio to watch more.
